# Code owners — the approval gate for the canonical runtime registry.
#
# In this repo, a runtime is *accepted* when its manifest is merged under
# `registry/runtimes/`. Requiring code-owner review on that path (plus branch
# protection with "Require review from Code Owners" enabled) is what makes a
# merge equivalent to approval. See GOVERNANCE.md.
#
# NOTE for repo admins: replace the placeholder owner below with a real team or
# user handle, and enable the branch-protection rule so this is enforced.

# The accepted-runtime source manifests: acceptance decisions live here.
/registry/                              @OpenCoven/runtime-maintainers

# The compiled index is generated — guard it so it can only change via a rebuild
# reviewed alongside its source manifest.
/crates/coven-runtime-registry/canonical/  @OpenCoven/runtime-maintainers

# The SDK crates and shared spec/schema.
/crates/                                @OpenCoven/runtime-maintainers
/schema/                                @OpenCoven/runtime-maintainers

# Governance, acceptance criteria, and the release/publish pipeline.
/GOVERNANCE.md                          @OpenCoven/runtime-maintainers
/.github/                               @OpenCoven/runtime-maintainers
